The wife of Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau has recovered from Coronavirus. Sophie Gregoire Trudeau took to her Facebook page on Saturday night to confirm that she is better and has been given an all-clear from her physician. Trudeau went into self-isolation after his wife tested positive. She wrote: “I wanted to give you all an update: I am feeling so much better and have received the all-clear from my physician and Ottawa Public Health. “From the bottom of my heart, I want to say thank you to everyone who reached out to me with their good wishes. “To everyone who is suffering right now, I send you all my love.” Meanwhile, Justin Trudeau had pledged $82 billion to offset losses caused by the outbreak of Coronavirus Globally, about 471,000 people have been infected by the deadly virus since its outbreak in Wuhan, China.